---
// Partnerships.astro — DS-08
---

<section id="partnerships" class="relative bg-navy">
  <!-- Amber rule -->
  <div class="rule-amber"></div>

  <div class="max-w-content mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 py-20 md:py-[120px]">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="reveal mb-16">
      <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[18px] text-cyan uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-4">PARTNERSHIP SCHEMES</p>
      <h2 class="font-grotesk font-bold text-off-white mb-5" style="font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 56px); letter-spacing: -0.02em; max-width: 700px;">
        Four schemes. One for every partner type.
      </h2>
      <p class="font-grotesk text-mid-grey text-lg" style="max-width: 600px; line-height: 1.65;">
        DigiSite doesn't offer a single generic partnership. Each scheme is built around the specific asset, commercial position, and priorities of a different type of partner. Find your scheme below.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Section image -->
    <div class="reveal mb-12 overflow-hidden rounded-md bg-navy">
      <img
        src="/partnerships-combined.jpeg"
        alt="DigiScaff and DigiPerim products deployed together on a UK construction site showing both product lines"
        width="1536"
        height="1024"
        loading="lazy"
        class="w-full object-contain"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Sticky scheme selector -->
    <div id="scheme-selector-bar" class="sticky top-[72px] z-40 -mx-6 md:-mx-12 px-6 md:px-12 mb-12" style="background: rgba(13, 27, 42, 0.96); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.12);">
      <div class="max-w-content mx-auto flex items-center h-[52px] gap-4 md:gap-8 overflow-x-auto" style="-webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; scrollbar-width: none;">
        <button class="scheme-selector-item active whitespace-nowrap font-grotesk font-medium text-[15px] tracking-[0.04em] text-off-white border-b-2 border-cyan pb-1 transition-all duration-200" data-target="scheme-construction">Construction & Development</button>
        <button class="scheme-selector-item whitespace-nowrap font-grotesk font-medium text-[15px] tracking-[0.04em] text-mid-grey border-b-2 border-transparent pb-1 transition-all duration-200" data-target="scheme-landlords">Landlords & Landowners</button>
        <button class="scheme-selector-item whitespace-nowrap font-grotesk font-medium text-[15px] tracking-[0.04em] text-mid-grey border-b-2 border-transparent pb-1 transition-all duration-200" data-target="scheme-commercial">Commercial & Public</button>
        <button class="scheme-selector-item whitespace-nowrap font-grotesk font-medium text-[15px] tracking-[0.04em] text-mid-grey border-b-2 border-transparent pb-1 transition-all duration-200" data-target="scheme-events">Events</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PANEL 1: Construction & Development -->
    <div id="scheme-construction" class="scheme-panel reveal bg-section rounded-md p-8 md:p-12 mb-6">
      <div class="h-px bg-cyan/40 -mx-8 md:-mx-12 -mt-8 md:-mt-12 mb-8 md:mb-12"></div>

      <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan/60 mb-2">SCHEME 01</p>
      <h3 class="font-grotesk font-bold text-off-white mb-3" style="font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 44px); letter-spacing: -0.02em;">Construction & Development</h3>
      <p class="font-grotesk text-mid-grey text-[20px] mb-10">Turn your scaffold pipeline into a recurring revenue stream.</p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[40%_60%] gap-10 mb-12">
        <!-- Left: Who + What -->
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-4">FOR</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Scaffold companies with a pipeline of contracted sites</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Principal contractors managing their own scaffold</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Building companies with control of their site perimeter</p>
          </div>

          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-4">WHAT YOU RECEIVE</p>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Revenue share on every site in your pipeline</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Zero upfront cost &mdash; DigiSite funds hardware and installation</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>DigiSite manages planning, power, advertising sales</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Site power supply at cost via DNO sub-metering</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Monthly revenue reports with proof-of-play</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: Proposition -->
        <div>
          <p class="font-grotesk font-bold text-[20px] text-off-white mb-5" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
            Your scaffold generates work for your clients. With DigiSite, it generates income for you.
          </p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.75;">
            Every site in your pipeline is a potential DigiSite location. You share your forward programme &mdash; sites contracted or in tender, with approximate dates and locations. DigiSite assesses each one, handles planning consent, and deploys on every qualifying site. You earn a revenue share on every screen that goes live.
          </p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey mt-4" style="line-height: 1.75;">
            This is the pipeline model: the partnership comes first, sites flow from it. The more active sites you carry, the more you earn. And because DigiSite is already on your site managing power infrastructure, there's a direct operational benefit before the first advertisement ever runs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tier model -->
      <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-6">VOLUME TIER MODEL &mdash; REVENUE SHARE INCREASES WITH ACTIVE SITES</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-3 mb-4">
        <div class="p-5 border border-cyan/[0.15] rounded bg-cyan/[0.04]">
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-2">TIER 1</p>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[22px] text-off-white">1&ndash;4</p>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase text-mid-grey mb-2">SITES</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[12px] text-mid-grey">Standard onboarding, remote monitoring, proof-of-play</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 border border-cyan/[0.15] rounded bg-cyan/[0.05]">
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-2">TIER 2</p>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[22px] text-off-white">5&ndash;9</p>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase text-mid-grey mb-2">SITES</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[12px] text-mid-grey">Priority mobilisation + co-branding on canvas wrap</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 border border-cyan/[0.15] rounded bg-cyan/[0.06]">
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-2">TIER 3</p>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[22px] text-off-white">10&ndash;19</p>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase text-mid-grey mb-2">SITES</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[12px] text-mid-grey">Dedicated account contact + pipeline planning support</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 border border-cyan/35 rounded bg-cyan/[0.08]">
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-2">TIER 4</p>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[22px] text-cyan">20+</p>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase text-mid-grey mb-2">SITES</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[12px] text-mid-grey">First access to new products + joint business planning</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey text-center mb-10">
        Tier status is calculated on active live sites plus accumulated site history. The more you commit, the better your terms &mdash; and the more you earn.
      </p>

      <!-- Commercial strip -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 py-7 border-t border-b border-cyan/10 bg-cyan/[0.03] -mx-8 md:-mx-12 px-8 md:px-12 mb-10">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">AGREEMENT TYPE</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">Site licence under framework agreement</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">MINIMUM TERM</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">6 months (co-terminus with scaffold)</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">PAYMENT</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">Monthly in arrears</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">PLANNING COST</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">Funded entirely by DigiSite</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <button onclick="window.location.href='/contact?scheme=construction'" class="inline-block px-9 py-4 bg-cyan text-navy font-grotesk font-semibold text-[14px] tracking-[0.04em] rounded-sm hover:shadow-[0_0_24px_rgba(0,212,255,0.35)] transition-all duration-200">
        Join the Construction & Development Scheme &rarr;
      </button>
    </div>

    <!-- PANEL 2: Landlords & Landowners -->
    <div id="scheme-landlords" class="scheme-panel reveal bg-navy border border-cyan/[0.1] rounded-md p-8 md:p-12 mb-6">
      <div class="h-px bg-amber/40 -mx-8 md:-mx-12 -mt-8 md:-mt-12 mb-8 md:mb-12"></div>

      <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan/60 mb-2">SCHEME 02</p>
      <h3 class="font-grotesk font-bold text-off-white mb-3" style="font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 44px); letter-spacing: -0.02em;">Landlords & Landowners</h3>
      <p class="font-grotesk text-mid-grey text-[20px] mb-10">Your vacant site is costing you money. DigiSite changes that.</p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[40%_60%] gap-10 mb-12">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-4">FOR</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-amber mr-2">&rarr;</span>Property owners with vacant or underperforming sites</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-amber mr-2">&rarr;</span>Freeholders of buildings in planning limbo</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-amber mr-2">&rarr;</span>Owners of heritage properties requiring fabric repair</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-amber mr-2">&rarr;</span>Landowners with high-footfall frontage generating no income</p>
          </div>

          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-4">WHAT YOU RECEIVE</p>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-amber mr-2">&rarr;</span>A guaranteed minimum annual income from an idle asset</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-amber mr-2">&rarr;</span>Revenue share above a defined threshold</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-amber mr-2">&rarr;</span>No upfront cost &mdash; DigiSite funds scaffold, hardware, and planning</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-amber mr-2">&rarr;</span>Improved visual presentation of a neglected frontage</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-amber mr-2">&rarr;</span>A credible argument for planning authorities (community benefit)</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-grotesk font-bold text-[20px] text-off-white mb-5" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
            DigiSite doesn't need your site to be active. It needs it to be visible.
          </p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.75;">
            Vacant plots, empty buildings, sites stuck in planning &mdash; these assets are costing their owners money every month in rates, insurance and maintenance, generating nothing in return. DigiSite identifies sites with strong audience data, approaches the landowner, and proposes a ground licence that pays from day one.
          </p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey mt-4" style="line-height: 1.75;">
            DigiSite sources and erects any scaffold required. DigiSite applies for and funds planning consent. DigiSite manages all advertising. The landowner's contribution is access rights and a signature. The result is a new income stream from an asset that was previously a liability.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Heritage callout -->
      <div class="p-6 md:p-9 border border-amber/20 rounded-md bg-amber/[0.04] mb-10">
        <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-amber mb-3">HERITAGE & LISTED BUILDINGS</p>
        <h4 class="font-grotesk font-bold text-[18px] text-off-white mb-3">
          A deteriorating listed building is a planning problem. DigiSite can help make it a planning solution.
        </h4>
        <p class="font-grotesk text-[14px] text-mid-grey mb-4" style="line-height: 1.65;">
          Where scaffold is required for inspection, stabilisation or repair, DigiSite can monetise that scaffold during the works period. Revenue generated by the screens can be ring-fenced toward fabric repair costs &mdash; a material consideration that planning authorities weigh favourably. Community art content displayed during advertising downtime further strengthens the planning case. DigiSite can help turn a liability into a demonstrable public benefit.
        </p>
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-mid-grey/60 mt-4">
          Grade I and II* listed buildings carry very high planning risk and are assessed on a case-by-case basis. Grade II listed buildings are the primary heritage opportunity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Commercial strip -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 py-7 border-t border-b border-cyan/10 bg-cyan/[0.03] -mx-8 md:-mx-12 px-8 md:px-12 mb-10">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">AGREEMENT TYPE</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">Ground licence agreement</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">MINIMUM TERM</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">24 months (36&ndash;48 preferred)</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">PAYMENT</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">Guaranteed minimum + revenue share</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">PLANNING COST</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">Funded entirely by DigiSite</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <button onclick="window.location.href='/contact?scheme=landlords'" class="inline-block px-9 py-4 border border-amber text-amber font-grotesk font-semibold text-[14px] tracking-[0.04em] rounded-sm hover:bg-amber/10 transition-all duration-200">
        Discuss a Landlords & Landowners Scheme &rarr;
      </button>
    </div>

    <!-- PANEL 3: Commercial & Public -->
    <div id="scheme-commercial" class="scheme-panel reveal bg-section rounded-md p-8 md:p-12 mb-6">
      <div class="h-px bg-cyan/40 -mx-8 md:-mx-12 -mt-8 md:-mt-12 mb-8 md:mb-12"></div>

      <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan/60 mb-2">SCHEME 03</p>
      <h3 class="font-grotesk font-bold text-off-white mb-3" style="font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 44px); letter-spacing: -0.02em;">Commercial & Public</h3>
      <p class="font-grotesk text-mid-grey text-[20px] mb-10">High-footfall sites. Captive audiences. Revenue from a boundary that costs you nothing to maintain.</p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[40%_60%] gap-10 mb-12">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-4">FOR</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Retail park and drive-thru operators</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Supermarket and leisure destination estate teams</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Local authorities with public realm or infrastructure works</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-off-white" style="line-height: 1.8;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>NHS trusts and housing associations with estate programmes</p>
          </div>

          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-4">WHAT YOU RECEIVE (COMMERCIAL)</p>
          <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Revenue share from advertising on your site boundary</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Free screen time allocation for your own promotional content</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>DigiSite manages all advertisers and content &mdash; zero admin</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>National estate agreements for multi-site operators</p>
          </div>

          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-4">WHAT YOU RECEIVE (PUBLIC SECTOR)</p>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Screens at no cost to the council or authority</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Free inventory: 25&ndash;30% of screen time for public information</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>Community art and local authority content in downtime</p>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.7;"><span class="text-cyan mr-2">&rarr;</span>DigiSite generates and shares advertising revenue</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-grotesk font-bold text-[20px] text-off-white mb-5" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
            A drive-thru queue is a captive audience with dwell time. That's exactly what advertisers want to reach.
          </p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey" style="line-height: 1.75;">
            Commercial sites &mdash; drive-thrus, retail parks, car park perimeters, leisure destinations &mdash; are built around high volumes of passing and dwelling people. DigiPerim is purpose-built for exactly these environments: standalone perimeter framework, no scaffold required, full front-access maintenance, fast to deploy and recover.
          </p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[15px] text-mid-grey mt-4" style="line-height: 1.75;">
            For large commercial operators managing national estates, DigiSite offers a Master Site Licence &mdash; one agreement covering all sites. Individual site schedules are appended as screens are deployed. A conversation with the right person in an estates team can unlock dozens of locations from a single agreement.
          </p>

          <!-- Public sector callout -->
          <div class="mt-8 p-6 border border-cyan/[0.12] rounded-md bg-cyan/[0.03]">
            <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-cyan mb-3">PUBLIC SECTOR & COUNCILS</p>
            <h4 class="font-grotesk font-bold text-[18px] text-off-white mb-3">Screens that inform, connect and pay for themselves.</h4>
            <p class="font-grotesk text-[14px] text-mid-grey mb-4" style="line-height: 1.65;">
              DigiSite's offer to a local authority is straightforward: screens deployed at no cost during public realm or infrastructure works, with a defined free inventory allocation for council communications, public health campaigns, local arts content, and community announcements. DigiSite monetises the remaining inventory and shares the revenue. The council gains a communications platform and an income stream from works that would otherwise generate neither.
            </p>
            <p class="font-grotesk font-medium text-[13px] text-off-white">
              DigiSite is actively seeking its first local authority partnership. Liverpool City Council's public art programme makes them a natural first conversation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Commercial strip -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 py-7 border-t border-b border-cyan/10 bg-cyan/[0.03] -mx-8 md:-mx-12 px-8 md:px-12 mb-10">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">AGREEMENT TYPE</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">Site licence / Master Site Licence</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">TERM</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">12&ndash;36 months commercial &middot; aligned to works (public)</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">FREE INVENTORY</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">10&ndash;15% commercial &middot; 25&ndash;30% public sector</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono font-semibold text-[12px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cyan mb-1">PLANNING COST</p>
          <p class="font-grotesk text-[13px] text-mid-grey">Funded entirely by DigiSite</p>
        </div>
